description: This source file implements the data model library initialization and management functions for a COSA (COSI on System Architecture) based system. It includes functions to create, initialize, and remove a backend manager object, which manages system components like device info. The file is part of a larger project related to network or device management, with references to licensing information and object lifecycle management.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE CosaBackEndManagerCreate(VOID)
methods.description: Constructs a COSA backend manager object by allocating memory and initializing core function pointers and object ID.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS CosaBackEndManagerInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes the backend manager object, primarily by creating and setting up device info, and logs the process.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS CosaBackEndManagerRemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Removes and frees the backend manager object memory.
